# 12. 扉を開く勇気を

MEIKO: I see. I'm sorry you had to go through something so awful.
Kohane: Um, I'm sorry...for just unloading on you like this...
MEIKO: Don't you worry about that. I think this calls for a glass of warm milk with plenty of honey.
Kohane: Thank you so much.
Len: How are you feeling? Any better?
Kohane: Yeah... Thank you.
Kohane: .....
Kohane: I'm no good at this...
Kohane: After An shared her dream with me, I decided to sing as best I could...
Kohane: But I just wasn't serious enough about it...
Len: .....
Kohane: After all that, I haven't been able to change one bit...
Len: That's not true at all. Just look at how much this is bothering you, Kohane!
Kohane: .....
MEIKO: Len's right. The fact that you're worrying so much about this is proof that you want things to change—that you're trying desperately to open the next door.
Kohane: The next door?
Kohane: Oh...
Kohane: That's right. I made up my mind that I'd go listen to that song again!
Kohane: So... I've got to open the door!
Kohane: But...I...
Miku: Whether you're going to stop here or step through that next door is up to you.
Kohane: .....
Miku: What do you think your true feelings are, Kohane?
Kohane: My true feelings...?
Kohane: I'm not sure, but...
An: ♪ ——! ——! ——!!
Kohane: ——♪ ——♪
Kohane: The first time I sang at the cafe was so fun. My heart was racing.
Kohane: I just can't get that feeling out of my head. That's why I was so happy when An invited me to team up with her.
Kohane: I couldn't help but wonder how great it would be to chase after a dream together.
Miku: Right?
Kohane: .....
Kohane: So...
Kohane: I guess my true feelings...
Miku: Kohane, no matter what happens or what anyone says to you, there is no need to change those feelings you already have.
Miku: They are yours and nobody else's. They're precious, and I think they are worth cherishing.
Kohane: .....
Kohane: My... My true feelings...
Kohane: I want to sing with An!
Kohane: And together, I want to put on an event that will surpass RAD WEEKEND!
Miku: I think that sounds wonderful.
Kohane: Miku...
Kohane: I need to go tell An!
Len: Good luck! We believe in you!
Kohane: MEIKO... Len... Thank you so much, everyone!
Miku: Looks like one of them was able to find their true feelings.
MEIKO: You're right. And it would seem Untitled is one step closer to becoming a song.
Len: Hehe. I hope we'll be able to sing it with them soon!
Miku: Right?
Miku: Good luck, Kohane.
Kohane: .....
Kohane: I've got to change even more...so An and I will be able to put on the greatest event ever.
An's Father: An, you're spacing out again.
An: Oh, yeah. Sorry.
An's Father: Looks like we're getting low on whiskey. I'm going to grab some from the back.
An: Okay.
An: (I can see that she read my messages, but she still hasn't responded...)
An: (I wasn't able to look after Kohane like I should have. So much for telling her I'd help her.)
An: (I was really looking forward to teaching her more about this town and watching her enjoy all the events...)
An: (But now...)
An: Sorry, Dad! I need to go see Kohane so I can—
Kohane's Voice: An...
An: Huh? Kohane?
